1. Actors (User Types)

• End User (Member): Day-to-day tenant user, limited permissions.

• Admin (Tenant Admin): Manages tenant users and settings.

• Developer (API Consumer): Integrates via tenant-scoped API tokens.

• System Admin: Platform-level maintenance and global tenant management.

2. Core Workflows

• Onboarding: Signup -> Create/Join Tenant -> Dashboard.

• Tenant Lifecycle: Configuration -> Invitations -> Active Work -> Deletion.

• API/Dev: Token generation -> Scoped API calls -> Usage logging.

• Admin/Ops: RBAC management, audit log review, and platform health monitoring.

3. Backend Features (The "Surface Area")

• Auth & Identity: Login, Sessions, JWT, Profile management.

• Tenant/RBAC: Isolation logic, Role definitions, Permission checks.

• Resources: CRUD for "Projects" (Tenant-scoped).

• Files: Upload/Download with metadata and resource association.

• Audit: Detailed logging for user activity, admin actions, and API events.

4. Frontend Components

• Auth pages, Tenant Selector, Resource CRUD UI, File Manager, API Token Management, and Audit Feed.

5. Strategy

• Focus: Auth/Authz, Tenant Isolation, RBAC, API/UI Parity, Auditability.

• Excluded: Payments, Messaging, Real-time (to focus on ProdSec).


